# Pick ONE auth mode.
#
# Token-only (recommended — lowest standing privilege): a short-lived
# registration token per repo. Agents register once; credentials persist in the
# mounted volume and are reused on every restart, so the tokens are spent after
# first boot and nothing with admin rights lives on the host. Var name is
# REG_TOKEN_<REPO>, repo uppercased with non-alphanumerics -> '_'.
# Mint one per repo:
#   gh api -X POST repos/<ORG>/<repo>/actions/runners/registration-token --jq .token
REG_TOKEN_VSCODE_ALTERMINAL=
REG_TOKEN_CLAUDEPILOT=

# PAT (alternative — recreate-resilient, but a durable admin credential on the
# host): a fine-grained PAT with repo Administration:read+write on every repo in
# REPOS. The container mints a registration token per repo on every boot and
# deregisters on shutdown. Comment out the REG_TOKEN_* lines if you use this.
# ACCESS_TOKEN=
